        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The following code\r\n{code}\r\n$locale = new Zend_Locale('fr_FR');\r\nprint_r($locale->getQuestion());\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nwill return \r\n{code}\r\nArray\r\n(\r\n    [yes] => oui\r\n    [no] => non\r\n    [yesarray] => Array\r\n        (\r\n            [0] => oui\r\n            [1] => o\r\n        )\r\n\r\n    [noarray] => Array\r\n        (\r\n            [0] => non\r\n            [1] => n\r\n        )\r\n\r\n    [yesexpr] => ^([oO]([uU][iI])?)|([oO]?)\r\n    [noexpr] => ^([nN]([oO][nN])?)|([nN]?)\r\n)\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThen {code}\r\npreg_match('\/^([oO]([uU][iI])?)|([oO]?)\/', 'any string even an empty one')\r\n{code}\r\nwill always be 1 because of the :\r\n\r\n[yesexpr] => ^([oO]([uU][iI])?)*{color:red}|([oO]?){color}*\r\n\r\nThen I think that a correction for this issue would be changing these lines in *Zend\/Locale.php* : \r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif ($one === false) {\r\n    $regex .= ')';\r\n}\r\n\r\n$regex .= '?)';\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nby\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif ($one === false) {\r\n    $regex .= ')?)';\r\n} else {\r\n    $regex .= ')';\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe bug is independant of the locale.\r\n\r\n"
